	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001238_0001"/><!--pb/@n='95r'--> 
<!--printed letterhead--><!--
<p rend="center"><placeName>50A Albemarle Street, London, W.</placeName></p>
--><!--end of printed letterhead-->
<lb/><p rend="right">16 Feby 1858</p>
<lb/><p>My dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>As it is desirable 
<lb/>that an abridgement 
<lb/>of my work 
<lb/>the Missionary 
<lb/>travels should 
<lb/>be issued and 
<lb/>I have the fullest 
<lb/>confidence 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001238_0002"/><!--pb/@n='95v'--> 
<lb/>in <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Elwin<reg>'</reg>s</persName>
<lb/>ability and sympathy 
<lb/>for such abridgement 
<lb/>and in your 
<lb/>management of 
<lb/>it I hereby 
<lb/><del type="strikethrough">by</del> authorize 
<lb/>you to take 
<lb/>whatever steps 
<lb/>you may 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001238_0003"/><!--pb/@n='96r'--> 
<lb/>deem advisable 
<lb/>in the matter 
<lb/>and I leave it 
<lb/>entirely to your 
<lb/>judgment as 
<lb/>to the time &amp;c 
<lb/>of publication<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am &amp;</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p><persName>John Murray</persName> Esq</p>
			
</div>
